<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="526" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,259,1258]" pageId="5" pageNumber="526">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1195,1221]" pageId="5" pageNumber="526">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific epithet is derived from the Latin 
<emphasis box="[856,887,1195,1221]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="526">bi-</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis box="[942,1046,1195,1221]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="526">hamatilis</emphasis>
, referring to the two hooked distal processes of the aedeagus.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
